            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EGod%20always%20starts%20His%20process%20of%20purifying%20in%20His%20own%20house.%20In%20the%20New%20Testament%2C%20Peter%20echoed%20that%20thought%2C%20saying%20that%20judgment%20must%20%22begin%20first%20among%20God's%20own%20children%22%20(1%20Peter%204%3A17).%20What%20a%20sober%20realization%20that%20judgment%20begins%20first%20among%20God's%20people!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EEzekiel%209%20speaks%20of%20a%20man%20dressed%20in%20linen%20who%20was%20carrying%20a%20writer's%20case.%20The%20man%20was%20instructed%20to%20walk%20through%20the%20city%20of%20Jerusalem%20and%20put%20a%20mark%20on%20the%20forehead%20of%20every%20person%20who%20had%20wept%20and%20sighed%20because%20of%20the%20sins%20they%20saw%20taking%20place%20around%20them%20(v.%204).%20Apparently%2C%20there%20were%20those%20who%20grieved%20deeply%20for%20the%20sins%20of%20their%20society.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20average%20person%20today%20has%20no%20concern%20for%20the%20gross%20immorality%20and%20debauchery%20existing%20in%20our%20society.%20Such%20an%20individual%20thinks%20homosexuality%20is%20%22gay%2C%22%20abortion%20is%20%22necessary%2C%22%20and%20drunkenness%20and%20adultery%20are%20%22acceptable.%22%20For%20God's%20saints%2C%20however%2C%20these%20things%20should%20be%20repulsive%20and%20deeply%20grievous.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20marked%20Noah%20as%20righteous%20in%20his%20generation%20and%20spared%20only%20his%20family%20from%20the%20flood%20that%20enveloped%20the%20earth.%20Even%20now%20God%20is%20%22marking%20the%20foreheads%22%20of%20those%20whose%20lives%20are%20pure%20and%20who%20closely%20follow%20His%20commands.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERemember%3A%20This%20process%20begins%20in%20the%20sanctuary%2C%20so%20check%20your%20%22mark%22%20today.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
